The main purpose of computing derivatives in the gradient descent algorithm is to identify local minima.

00:11.600 --> 00:19.080
And so in this video I'm going to explain what minima and maxima are, how we use the derivative to

00:19.120 --> 00:27.400
find these critical points, and how to distinguish local minima from local maxima using the derivative.

00:28.160 --> 00:28.440
Okay.

