So it turns out that the derivative can tell us exactly where these minima and maxima points are.

01:28.840 --> 01:30.760
So here is the derivative.

01:30.760 --> 01:34.640
So this green line shows the derivative of this function.

01:35.080 --> 01:39.240
And now it turns out that all of the extreme points.

01:39.240 --> 01:40.960
So the minima and maxima.

01:41.160 --> 01:45.240
In the parlance of calculus these are called the critical points.

01:45.760 --> 01:49.880
They are associated with a derivative of zero.

01:50.440 --> 01:57.880
So where the function is maximum and where the function is minimum, the derivative has a value of zero.

01:58.080 --> 01:59.400
So we can see that here.

01:59.400 --> 02:01.320
Here's the function in the blue line.

